                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6775/129.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Honduras</gloss> to
                        President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa, Honduras</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-09-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 22, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am glad to answer Your Excellency’s courteous message of yesterday by saying
                    that I appreciate, to their high value, the good offices of Your Excellency and
                    the Most Excellent President of Mexico toward insuring the maintenance of peace
                    in Central America, and that I accept with the greatest pleasure the invitation
                    to the conference that is to meet in Washington in November next and to which I
                    will immediately appoint the representatives of Honduras.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Miguel R. Dávila.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
